<paragraph id="8BABA84BFF85FFC4B1803059FDD8FB4D" blockId="9.[384,558,1139,1160]" box="[384,558,1139,1160]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">
<heading id="D0E31F27FF85FFC4B1803059FDD8FB4D" box="[384,558,1139,1160]" centered="true" fontSize="8" level="2" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" reason="8">
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B1803059FDD8FB4D" baseAuthorityName="Shimizu" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[384,558,1139,1160]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ctenocerinae">CTENOCERINAE</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BABA84BFF85FFC4B0A430B3FEDCF8A5" blockId="9.[164,779,1177,1903]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">
This subfamily was first proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF85FFC4B24D30B3FD10FB65" author="Haupt H" box="[589,742,1177,1199]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" pagination="109 - 197" refId="ref11269" refString="Haupt H. 1929. Weiterer ausbau meines Systems der Psammocharidae. Mit Beschreibung neuer gatungen und arten. Mitteilungen aus dem Zoologischen Museum in Berlin 15: 109 - 197." type="journal article" year="1929">Haupt (1929)</bibRefCitation>
, as 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B0A43092FEDEFB04" box="[164,296,1208,1230]" pageId="9" pageNumber="284" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Claveliinae">Claveliinae</taxonomicName>
, to separate its members from 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B29D3092FCF1FB04" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[669,775,1208,1230]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
; it includes two genera in the Neotropics, four in 
<collectingCountry id="F303E8DBFF85FFC4B2D630FCFF11FAC1" name="Australia" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Australia</collectingCountry>
, and 
<quantity id="4CEC05AEFF85FFC4B12E30DFFE9DFAC1" box="[302,363,1269,1291]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.794" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" unit="in" value="11.0">11 in</quantity>
Africa. The name was changed to 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B0A43139FE0DFAE3" authority="(Shimizu, 1994)" baseAuthorityName="Shimizu" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[164,507,1299,1321]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ctenocerinae">
Ctenocerinae (
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF85FFC4B14A3139FE02FAE3" author="Shimizu A" box="[330,500,1299,1321]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" pagination="1 - 142" refId="ref12270" refString="Shimizu A. 1994. Phylogeny and classification of the family Pompilidae (Hymenoptera). Tokyo Metropolitan University Bulletin of Natural History 2: 1 - 142." type="journal article" year="1994">Shimizu, 1994</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, but the composition of this subfamily remained mostly stable, except for a suggestion to include 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B17A317BFDCAFAAD" authority="Banks" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1938" box="[378,572,1361,1383]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Apinaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B17A317BFE1DFAAC" box="[378,491,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Apinaspis</emphasis>
Banks
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B27A317BFE98FA4F" authority="(Pitts et al., 2006)" baseAuthorityName="Pitts" baseAuthorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Epipompilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B27A317BFCFDFAAC" box="[634,779,1361,1382]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Epipompilus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF85FFC4B0AC3145FE93FA4F" author="Pitts JP &amp; Wasbauer MS &amp; von Dohlen CD" box="[172,357,1391,1413]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" pagination="63 - 84" refId="ref11898" refString="Pitts JP, Wasbauer MS, von Dohlen CD. 2006. Preliminary morphological analysis of relationships between the spider wasp subfamilies (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae): revisiting an old problem. Zoologica Scripta 35: 63 - 84." type="journal article" year="2006">
Pitts 
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B0E8315AFEEEFA4E" box="[232,280,1391,1413]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">et al</emphasis>
., 2006
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B1783145FDF3FA4E" box="[376,517,1391,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Epipompilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B1783145FDF3FA4E" box="[376,517,1391,1412]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Epipompilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is discussed below (see 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B0A431A4FEFDFA6E" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[164,267,1422,1444]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
section), whereas 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B1E931A4FDACFA69" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1938" box="[489,602,1422,1443]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Apinaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B1E931A4FDACFA69" box="[489,602,1422,1443]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Apinaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is an Oriental monotypic genus (
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF85FFC4B1793186FDFFFA08" author="Banks N" box="[377,521,1452,1474]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" pagination="237 - 249" refId="ref10210" refString="Banks N. 1938. Some Psammocharidae from Singapore. Proceedings from the Entomological Society of Washington 40: 237 - 249." type="journal article" year="1938">Banks, 1938</bibRefCitation>
) and has characteristics similar to the Australian genera described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF85FFC4B2C631E1FF18F9CA" author="Evans HE" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" pagination="244 - 252" refId="ref11054" refString="Evans HE. 1972. The tribe Ctenoceratini in Australia (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Australian Journal of Entomology 11: 244 - 252." type="journal article" year="1972">Evans (1972)</bibRefCitation>
. We support the classification of 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B27831C0FD1FFA35" authorityName="Banks" authorityYear="1938" box="[632,745,1514,1535]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Apinaspis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B27831C0FD1FFA35" box="[632,745,1514,1535]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Apinaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B0A43222FEF8F9D4" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[164,270,1544,1566]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
, as proposed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF85FFC4B1D33222FD72F9D4" author="Shimizu A" box="[467,644,1544,1566]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" pagination="1 - 142" refId="ref12270" refString="Shimizu A. 1994. Phylogeny and classification of the family Pompilidae (Hymenoptera). Tokyo Metropolitan University Bulletin of Natural History 2: 1 - 142." type="journal article" year="1994">Shimizu (1994)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF85FFC4B2C23222FF1BF9F7" author="Banks N" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" pagination="237 - 249" refId="ref10210" refString="Banks N. 1938. Some Psammocharidae from Singapore. Proceedings from the Entomological Society of Washington 40: 237 - 249." type="journal article" year="1938">Banks (1938)</bibRefCitation>
, until further analyses suggest otherwise. Although these African, Neotropical, and Oriental/ Australian taxa share several morphological features – a large antennal scrobe, a transverse groove on the second sternite that is usually prolonged to vertex, and a hind tibia with short spines directed straight backwards – these may be adaptations for preying on trapdoor spiders (
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF85FFC4B14732D7FE21F8D9" author="Evans HE" box="[327,471,1789,1811]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" pagination="244 - 252" refId="ref11054" refString="Evans HE. 1972. The tribe Ctenoceratini in Australia (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Australian Journal of Entomology 11: 244 - 252." type="journal article" year="1972">Evans, 1972</bibRefCitation>
) that were independently acquired. More information on behaviour is needed, as the natural history of these taxa remains poorly understood.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C30EFBC0FF85FFC4B35334ECFA62FAE3" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BABA84BFF85FFC4B35334ECFA56FD81" blockId="9.[826,1441,198,1321]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">
Our analyses did not recover the monophyly of 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B33A34CEFC25FF30" baseAuthorityName="Shimizu" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[826,979,228,250]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ctenocerinae">Ctenocerinae</taxonomicName>
. The Neotropical 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B4A334CEFAC8FF33" authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1930" box="[1187,1342,228,249]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Lepidocnemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B4A334CEFAC8FF33" box="[1187,1342,228,249]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Lepidocnemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and the Australian 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B3C93529FBB7FED2" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1855" box="[969,1089,259,280]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Maurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B3C93529FBB7FED2" box="[969,1089,259,280]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Maurillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are nested within different nonctenocerine lineages with high support. The morphological similarities of these and the African ctenocerine genera must now be interpreted as convergent traits. Four Australian taxa assigned to 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B33A35B6FC26FE78" baseAuthorityName="Shimizu" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[826,976,412,434]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ctenocerinae">Ctenocerinae</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF85FFC4B3FC35B6FB65FE78" author="Evans HE" box="[1020,1171,412,434]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" pagination="244 - 252" refId="ref11054" refString="Evans HE. 1972. The tribe Ctenoceratini in Australia (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Australian Journal of Entomology 11: 244 - 252." type="journal article" year="1972">Evans (1972)</bibRefCitation>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B4A335B6FA6BFE7B" authority="Evans" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1972" box="[1187,1437,412,433]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Cteniziphontes" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B4A335B6FABCFE7B" box="[1187,1354,412,433]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Cteniziphontes</emphasis>
Evans
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B33A3590FBE4FE1A" authority="Evans" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1972" box="[826,1042,442,464]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Apoclavelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B33A3590FC4BFE05" box="[826,957,442,463]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Apoclavelia</emphasis>
Evans
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B4213590FB65FE05" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1855" box="[1057,1171,442,463]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Maurillus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B4213590FB65FE05" box="[1057,1171,442,463]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Maurillus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B4A43590FA6FFE1A" authority="Evans" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1972" box="[1188,1433,442,464]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Austroclavelia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B4A43590FAB1FE05" box="[1188,1351,442,463]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Austroclavelia</emphasis>
Evans
</taxonomicName>
) and the three genera discussed by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF85FFC4B4DA35F3FC77FDC4" author="Waichert C &amp; Pitts JP" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" pagination="1279 - 1284" refId="ref12548" refString="Waichert C, Pitts JP. 2011. Description of a new Abernessia with notes on Neotropical Ctenocerinae (Hymenoptera: Pompilidae). Annals of the Entomological Society of America 104: 1279 - 1284." type="journal article" year="2011">Waichert &amp; Pitts (2011)</bibRefCitation>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B39435D2FBA6FDC4" authority="Arle" authorityName="Arle" authorityYear="1947" box="[916,1104,504,526]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Abernessia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B39435D2FBE6FDC7" box="[916,1040,504,525]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Abernessia</emphasis>
Arlé
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B45F35D2FB0DFDC7" authorityName="Haupt" authorityYear="1930" box="[1119,1275,504,525]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Lepidocnemis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B45F35D2FB0DFDC7" box="[1119,1275,504,525]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Lepidocnemis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B50E35D2FC53FDE6" authority="Ashmead" authorityName="Ashmead" authorityYear="1902" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Hypoferreola" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B50E35D2FA57FDC7" box="[1294,1441,504,525]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Hypoferreola</emphasis>
Ashmead
</taxonomicName>
) are herein transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B4E5363CFABAFDE6" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[1253,1356,534,556]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
on the basis of the molecular phylogeny and of morphology.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BABA84BFF85FFC4B3533679FA62FAE3" blockId="9.[826,1441,198,1321]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">
The monophyly of African 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B4773679FAF1FDA3" baseAuthorityName="Shimizu" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[1143,1287,595,617]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ctenocerinae">Ctenocerinae</taxonomicName>
(clade A) was recovered in all analyses. Although support for this clade was low in the unconstrained analyses, it was high in the clock-constrained analysis. We redefine 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B33A36E4FC26FD2E" baseAuthorityName="Shimizu" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[826,976,718,740]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ctenocerinae">Ctenocerinae</taxonomicName>
as the lineage represented by clade A, as it includes the nominal genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B4C636C7FAB7FCC8" authorityName="Dahlbom" authorityYear="1845" box="[1222,1345,749,770]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" genus="Ctenocerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9607459FF85FFC4B4C636C7FAB7FCC8" box="[1222,1345,749,770]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">Ctenocerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 11 Afro-tropical genera recognized by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF85FFC4B4BC3721FA92FCEB" author="Arnold G" box="[1212,1380,779,801]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" pagination="41 - 118" refId="ref9926" refString="Arnold G. 1932 b. The Psammocharidae of the Ethiopian region. Part 2. Subfamily Claveliinae, Haupt. Annals of the Transvaal Museum 15: 41 - 118." type="journal article" year="1932">Arnold (1932b)</bibRefCitation>
, with distribution extending into Java and 
<collectingCountry id="F303E8DBFF85FFC4B4CB3700FAF0FC8A" box="[1227,1286,810,832]" name="India" pageId="9" pageNumber="280">India</collectingCountry>
, should retain their classification as 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B42E3762FB36FC94" baseAuthorityName="Shimizu" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[1070,1216,840,862]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ctenocerinae">Ctenocerinae</taxonomicName>
until further analyses are performed. Males of all 11 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B4BC374DFAB8FCB7" baseAuthorityName="Shimizu" baseAuthorityYear="1994" box="[1212,1358,871,893]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Ctenocerinae">Ctenocerinae</taxonomicName>
genera designated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF85D5BAFF85FFC4B3E437AFFB66FC51" author="Arnold G" box="[996,1168,901,923]" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" pagination="41 - 118" refId="ref9926" refString="Arnold G. 1932 b. The Psammocharidae of the Ethiopian region. Part 2. Subfamily Claveliinae, Haupt. Annals of the Transvaal Museum 15: 41 - 118." type="journal article" year="1932">Arnold (1932b)</bibRefCitation>
are distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B33A378EFC55FC70" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[826,931,932,954]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
by having flagellum uni- or biramous, or crenulate antennae. These character states are not observed in 
<taxonomicName id="4C14D3C8FF85FFC4B3AE37CBFBEEFC3D" authorityName="Lepeletier de Saint Fargeau" authorityYear="1845" box="[942,1048,993,1015]" class="Insecta" family="Pompilidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="9" pageNumber="280" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Pepsinae">Pepsinae</taxonomicName>
. The subfamily is now recognized by (1) the metasomal sternum 2 with a distinct sharp transverse groove; (2) the mesofemur and the metafemur without subapical spine-like setae set in grooves or pits; (3) the metatibia without scale-like spines or serrate carina and with short, subequal spines directed straight backwards; and (4) the fore wing with first cubital vein (Cu1) simple at base, without any definite downward deflection; (5) the clypeus plate-like in shape; and (6) males with crenulate antennae. As far as we know, ctenocerine spider wasps prey on trap-door spiders.
</paragraph>
